      "hook": "You have an invisible leak. $111 a month.",
      "body_copy": "It's not the big grocery trips that drain your account.\n\nIt's Tuesday at 4pm. You're staring into the fridge, knowing there's food somewhere in there, but nothing connects into a meal.\n\nSo you grab your keys.\n\n$12 for rotisserie chicken. Again.\n$8 for pre-made salad. The third one this week.\n$15 for ingredients you'll use once.\n\nYou tell yourself it's just this once. But your bank statement knows better.\n\nThose small trips add up to $111 every month. Not because you're bad at budgeting. Because the system is broken.\n\nYou buy food. Good food. But it sits disconnected in your fridge like puzzle pieces that don't fit together.\n\nThe real cost isn't the money. It's that quiet moment every evening when you realize you're solving the same problem again. What's for dinner?\n\nYour kitchen is full of ingredients. Your mind is full of recipes you've saved. But there's no bridge between them.\n\nThat's the invisible leak. Not impulse buying. Not poor planning. The gap between having food and having meals.",
