      "platform": "Instagram",
      "hook": "That spinach you bought Monday? Gone by Thursday.",
      "body_copy": "You know the pattern by now.\n\nSunday: Cart full of good intentions. Fresh vegetables. Lean proteins. The works.\n\nMonday: Use some of the spinach in a smoothie.\n\nTuesday: Notice the spinach looking a little tired.\n\nWednesday: Tell yourself you'll use it tomorrow.\n\nThursday: Spinach goes straight to the bin.\n\nIt's not that you don't care. It's not that you don't try.\n\nYou planned to meal prep Sunday night. But soccer practice ran late.\n\nYou planned to cook Monday. But work exploded.\n\nYou planned to use everything Tuesday. But Emma had a meltdown and dinner became cereal.\n\nBy Wednesday, you're ordering takeout again because half your groceries are already past their prime.\n\nThe guilt sits heavy. Another $80 of groceries. Another week of good intentions gone wrong.\n\nYou're not failing at this.\n\nThe system is.",
