      "hook": "$1,336. That's what the average family loses every year.",
      "body_copy": "Not to groceries. To groceries that go bad.\n\nYou buy spinach with good intentions. It wilts in the crisper drawer. You grab ground beef on sale, then forget it's there until it's past its date.\n\nThe cilantro turns to mush. The bread grows spots. The leftovers get pushed to the back until they're unrecognizable.\n\nEvery week, the same cycle. Every month, money down the drain.",
