      "platform": "Instagram",
      "hook": "$1,336. That's what the average family loses every year.",
      "body_copy": "Not to theft. Not to emergencies.\n\nTo the gap between good intentions and what actually happens in your kitchen.\n\nYou buy fresh vegetables with a plan. They wilt in the crisper while you order takeout again.\n\nYou stock the pantry for home-cooked meals. The ingredients expire while you grab something quick on the way home.\n\nYou meal prep on Sunday. By Wednesday, those containers sit untouched while you stand in your kitchen, overwhelmed, reaching for your phone to order delivery.\n\nIt's the same pattern, week after week. The guilt compounds with every grocery receipt. Every expired item in the trash. Every delivery charge.\n\nYou're not failing at feeding your family.\n\nThe system you're trying to work within is broken. It assumes you have unlimited time, energy, and mental space to bridge the gap between buying food and actually cooking it.\n\nMost families lose over a thousand dollars annually to this invisible leak. Food waste. Convenience purchases. The premium you pay for quick solutions when your original plan falls apart.\n\nThe problem was never your willpower. It was never your cooking skills.\n\nThe system was disconnected from how your life actually works.",
