      "hook": "Five apps. None of them talk to each other.",
      "body_copy": "Your grocery app doesn't know what's in your recipe app. Your recipe app doesn't know what's in your pantry app. Your pantry app doesn't know what's on your meal planning app. Your meal planning app doesn't know what's on your grocery list.\n\nSo you're constantly switching between screens, double-checking, cross-referencing, and somehow still forgetting the one ingredient that makes the whole meal work.\n\nYou spend 5 to 10 hours a week just trying to figure out what to eat. Not cooking. Not enjoying meals with your family. Just... deciding.\n\nBecause the system is broken. These apps were built in isolation, each solving one tiny piece of the puzzle while completely ignoring how real families actually plan, shop, and cook.\n\nYou're not disorganized. You're not failing. You're trying to make a disconnected system work for a connected life.\n\nThe problem was never you.",
