      "platform": "Instagram",
      "hook": "The grocery app doesn't know your recipes.",
      "body_copy": "Your recipe app doesn't talk to your grocery app. Your grocery app doesn't know what's in your pantry. Your pantry doesn't connect to your meal planning.\n\nThree separate systems. Zero communication.\n\nSo you're stuck playing translator between all of them. Manually checking what you have. Manually adding ingredients. Manually figuring out what you can actually make with what's already home.\n\nNo wonder meal planning feels impossible. You're not managing one system — you're juggling three broken ones that were never designed to work together.\n\nThe average family spends 7 hours a week just trying to coordinate between these disconnected tools. That's not meal planning. That's digital chaos management.\n\nYou download the recipe app because it has beautiful photos. You use the grocery app because it's convenient. You try to meal plan because you want to save money and eat better.\n\nBut none of them know about each other. So you end up doing the same work three times, in three different places, hoping somehow it all connects.\n\nThe problem was never that you're bad at planning. The problem is you're trying to plan across a system that's fundamentally broken.\n\nDisconnected tools create disconnected results.",
