    {
      "id": "ec001-sp-038",
      "campaign_id": "EC-2026-001",
      "platform": "Instagram",
      "hook": "You tracked. You planned. You still threw out the spinach.",
      "body_copy": "The meal planning apps promised you'd save money. The budget spreadsheets said you'd stop wasting food. The grocery lists were supposed to fix everything.\n\nBut here you are, staring at wilted lettuce in your crisper drawer again.\n\nThe problem isn't your willpower. It's not your planning skills. It's not even your busy schedule.\n\nThe problem is that every system treats meal planning like it's separate from grocery shopping. And grocery shopping like it's separate from cooking. And cooking like it's separate from your actual life.\n\nYou plan meals on Sunday. Shop on Monday. Discover you're missing ingredients on Wednesday. Order takeout instead.\n\nYou buy ingredients for five meals. Cook two. Watch three expire.\n\nYou follow the grocery list perfectly. Come home to realize nothing actually works together.\n\nThe systems are disconnected. They don't talk to each other. They don't know about your Tuesday meeting that runs late or your kid's soccer practice or the fact that you hate chopping vegetables when you're tired.\n\nSo you end up spending 5 to 10 hours a week deciding what to eat, buying food that goes bad, and feeling like you're failing at something that should be simple.\n\nYou're not failing. The system is broken.",
      "cta": "Save this if the disconnected system sounds familiar",
      "hashtags": "#easychefpro #grocerybudget #foodwaste #mealplanningfails #savemoney #kitchenlife #momlife #instafood #momstagram #mealprepping #foodblogger #kitchenlife",
