      "id": "ec001-sp-044",
      "campaign_id": "EC-2026-001",
      "platform": "Instagram",
      "hook": "Monday meal plan. Wednesday takeout. Friday what's in the fridge?",
      "body_copy": "Sound familiar?\n\nYou start the week with good intentions. You plan meals, write lists, prep ingredients.\n\nBut by Wednesday, life happens. Soccer practice runs late. Work meeting goes over. The planned dinner needs ingredients you forgot to buy.\n\nSo you order takeout. Again.\n\nBy Friday, you're staring into the fridge playing 'what can I make from random leftovers?'\n\nHere's what nobody talks about: The problem isn't your planning skills. It's not your willpower. It's not even your busy schedule.\n\nThe problem is the system.\n\nTraditional meal planning treats each week like it exists in a vacuum. Plan Monday to Sunday. Start over. Repeat.\n\nBut your life doesn't work that way.\n\nYour pantry carries over. Your family's preferences evolve. Your schedule shifts. Your budget fluctuates.\n\nYet every planning system asks you to start fresh each week, ignoring everything that came before.\n\nNo wonder you're spending 5 to 10 hours a week deciding what to eat.\n\nThe system is disconnected from reality.\n\nYou're not failing at meal planning. Meal planning is failing you.",
