      "hook": "The spinach. The ground beef. The yogurt. $111 gone.",
      "body_copy": "Every month. Like clockwork.\n\nYou buy with good intentions. Tonight will be different. You'll cook that salmon. Use those bell peppers. Make something healthy.\n\nBut Tuesday becomes Wednesday becomes takeout again.\n\nThe groceries sit there, watching you order pizza. The milk expires. The herbs wilt. The chicken you swore you'd marinate gets tossed on Sunday.\n\n$111 worth of food that never became dinner.\n\nAnd it's not because you don't care. You do. You research recipes during lunch breaks. You pin meal ideas. You make lists.\n\nBut between work running late and soccer practice and that thing you forgot about, cooking becomes this impossible puzzle with missing pieces.\n\nSo you waste money on groceries you don't use. Then waste more money on food you don't really want.\n\nThe average family throws away $1,336 in unused food every year. Not because they're wasteful people. Because the system is broken.\n\nYou buy ingredients. But you don't have a plan that actually works with your real life.\n\nSo the cycle repeats. Good intentions. Good groceries. Bad timing. Wasted money.\n\nEvery single month.",
