      "campaign_id": "EC-2026-001",
      "platform": "Instagram",
      "hook": "$3.66 a day. The daily cost of the disconnect.",
      "body_copy": "That's $111 every month disappearing into the gap between good intentions and what actually happens.\n\nYou buy the groceries. You plan to cook. But something breaks down in between, and you're back to takeout again.\n\nIt's not the big grocery trips that hurt — it's the slow leak. The produce that goes bad. The ingredients bought for meals that never happen. The backup dinners that become the primary plan.\n\n$1,336 per year. That's the average cost families pay for food that never becomes dinner.\n\nNot because you don't care. Not because you don't try. Because the system has gaps, and groceries fall through them.\n\nYou see other families who seem to have it figured out. Their fridges stay organized. Their meal plans actually work. Their kids eat what's made.\n\nBut here's what they know that changes everything: the problem was never you.\n\nThe system was disconnected. There was no bridge between buying food and actually eating it. Between planning meals and having everything ready when dinner time hits.\n\nThat daily $3.66 isn't just money. It's the cost of a system that doesn't connect the dots.",
