      "platform": "Facebook",
      "hook": "The chicken that expired. The salad kit. The berries. Not your fault.",
      "body_copy": "The system is broken. You buy with good intentions, then watch $111/month turn into guilt in your fridge. That's $1,336/year of food that never becomes dinner. The planning apps don't connect to real grocery costs. The meal kits ignore what you already own. The recipes assume you have time you don't have. Meanwhile, the waste keeps adding up.",
