      "hook": "The invisible leak doesn't announce itself. It just drains.",
      "body_copy": "You bought groceries on Sunday. By Wednesday, you're ordering takeout again.\n\nThe lettuce wilts in the crisper. The chicken sits frozen while you scroll delivery apps. The pantry fills with good intentions that expire before they become meals.\n\n$111 every month disappears into food that never becomes dinner.\n\nIt's not the big purchases that break the budget. It's the slow bleed. The backup plans that become the main plan. The fresh ingredients that turn into guilt trips.\n\nYou know exactly what I mean. The moment you open the fridge, see everything you bought, and close it to order pizza instead.\n\nThat's $1,336 a year. Not on treats or splurges. On the gap between buying food and actually eating what you bought.\n\nThe system isn't working. The disconnect between your grocery cart and your dinner table costs real money. Every single week.\n\nThe leak keeps draining. The pattern keeps repeating. And the cost keeps adding up while perfectly good food sits untouched.",
